The Senator representing Taraba South and Senate deputy minority leader, Emmanuel Bwacha, has left the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) for the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC). The decampee was, on Thursday, led to the Presidential Villa, Abuja, by the chairman of the APC national interim committee, Governor Mai Mala Buni of Yobe State. He was formally received into the ruling APC by President Muhammadu Buhari.